474  /// copy constructor implementation
475  String::String(const String& obj) {
476  /// object member can be just copied by value
477  this->value = obj.value;
478 
479  /// if there is a token, make copy
480  if (obj.token) {
481  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
482  }
483 
484  /// set parents
485  set_parent_in_children();
486  }

548 
549  /// copy constructor implementation
550  Integer::Integer(const Integer& obj) {
551  /// object member can be just copied by value
552  this->value = obj.value;
553  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
554  if (obj.macro) {
555  this->macro.reset(obj.macro->clone());
556  }
557 
558  /// if there is a token, make copy
559  if (obj.token) {
560  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
561  }
562 
563  /// set parents
564  set_parent_in_children();
565  }
566 
567 
568  /// set this parent in the children
569  void Integer::set_parent_in_children() {
570 
571  /// optional member could be nullptr
572  if (macro) {
573  macro->set_parent(this);
574  }
575 
576  }

2491 /**
2492  * \brief Erase member to definitions

2496 }
2497 /**
2498  * \brief Erase members to definitions
2499  */
2500 AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator AssignedBlock::erase_assigned_definition(AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator first, AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator last) {
2501  return definitions.erase(first, last);
2502 }
2503 /**
2504  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to definitions
2505  *
2506  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
2507  */
2508 size_t AssignedBlock::erase_assigned_definition(std::unordered_set<AssignedDefinition*>& to_be_erased) {
2509  auto first = definitions.begin();
2510  auto last = definitions.end();
2511  auto result = first;
2512 
2513  while (first != last) {
2514  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
2515  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
2516  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
2517  reset_assigned_definition(result, *first);
2518  ++result;
2519  }
2520  ++first;
2521  }
2522 
2523  size_t out = last - result;
2524  erase_assigned_definition(result, last);
2525 
2526  return out;
2527 }

3006 /**
3007  * \brief Erase members to statements
3008  */
3009 StatementVector::const_iterator StatementBlock::erase_statement(StatementVector::const_iterator first, StatementVector::const_iterator last) {
3010  return statements.erase(first, last);
3011 }
3012 /**
3013  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to statements
3014  *
3015  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
3016  */
3017 size_t StatementBlock::erase_statement(std::unordered_set<Statement*>& to_be_erased) {
3018  auto first = statements.begin();
3019  auto last = statements.end();
3020  auto result = first;
3021 
3022  while (first != last) {
3023  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
3024  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
3025  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
3026  reset_statement(result, *first);
3027  ++result;
3028  }
3029  ++first;
3030  }
3031 
3032  size_t out = last - result;
3033  erase_statement(result, last);
3034 
3035  return out;
3036 }

4095  this->unit->accept(v);
4096  }
4097  (void)v;

4099  statement_block->accept(v);
4100  (void)v;

4139  /// copy constructor implementation
4140  ProcedureBlock::ProcedureBlock(const ProcedureBlock& obj) {
4141  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
4142  if (obj.name) {
4143  this->name.reset(obj.name->clone());
4144  }
4145  /// copy each element of vector
4146  for (auto& item : obj.parameters) {
4147  this->parameters.emplace_back(item->clone());
4148  }
4149  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
4150  if (obj.unit) {
4151  this->unit.reset(obj.unit->clone());
4152  }
4153  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
4154  if (obj.statement_block) {
4155  this->statement_block.reset(obj.statement_block->clone());
4156  }
4157 
4158  /// if there is a token, make copy
4159  if (obj.token) {
4160  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
4161  }
4162 
4163  /// set parents
4164  set_parent_in_children();
4165  }

6456 
6457  /// copy constructor implementation
6458  BinaryExpression::BinaryExpression(const BinaryExpression& obj) {
6459  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
6460  if (obj.lhs) {
6461  this->lhs.reset(obj.lhs->clone());
6462  }
6463  /// object member can be just copied by value
6464  this->op = obj.op;
6465  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
6466  if (obj.rhs) {
6467  this->rhs.reset(obj.rhs->clone());
6468  }
6469 
6470  /// if there is a token, make copy
6471  if (obj.token) {
6472  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
6473  }
6474 
6475  /// set parents
6476  set_parent_in_children();
6477  }
6478 
6479 
6480  /// set this parent in the children
6481  void BinaryExpression::set_parent_in_children() {
6482 
6483  /// optional member could be nullptr
6484  if (lhs) {
6485  lhs->set_parent(this);
6486  }
6487  op.set_parent(this);
6488  /// optional member could be nullptr
6489  if (rhs) {
6490  rhs->set_parent(this);
6491  }
6492 
6493  }
6494 
6495

6499  // set parents

6501  lhs->set_parent(this);
6502  }

7026  this->arguments.emplace_back(item->clone());

7050  }

7410  void FactorDef::visit_children(visitor::Visitor& v) {
7411  /// use -> for pointer member
7412  name->accept(v);
7413  (void)v;

7421  (void)v;

7424  this->gt->accept(v);
7425  }
7426  (void)v;
7427  /// optional member could be nullptr
7428  if (this->unit2) {
7429  this->unit2->accept(v);
7430  }
7431  (void)v;
7432  }

7823 /**
7824  * \brief Erase member to variables
7825  */
7826 LocalVarVector::const_iterator LocalListStatement::erase_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator first) {
7827  return variables.erase(first);
7828 }
7829 /**
7830  * \brief Erase members to variables
7831  */
7832 LocalVarVector::const_iterator LocalListStatement::erase_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator first, LocalVarVector::const_iterator last) {
7833  return variables.erase(first, last);
7834 }
7835 /**
7836  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to variables
7837  *
7838  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
7839  */
7840 size_t LocalListStatement::erase_local_var(std::unordered_set<LocalVar*>& to_be_erased) {
7841  auto first = variables.begin();
7842  auto last = variables.end();
7843  auto result = first;
7844 
7845  while (first != last) {
7846  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
7847  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
7848  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
7849  reset_local_var(result, *first);
7850  ++result;
7851  }
7852  ++first;
7853  }
7854 
7855  size_t out = last - result;
7856  erase_local_var(result, last);
7857 
7858  return out;
7859 }
7860

7862  * \brief Insert member to variables
7863  */
7864 LocalVarVector::const_iterator LocalListStatement::insert_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator position, const std::shared_ptr<LocalVar>& n) {
7865  n->set_parent(this);
7866  return variables.insert(position, n);
7867 }
7868 
7869 /**
7870  * \brief Reset member to variables
7871  */
7872 void LocalListStatement::reset_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator position, LocalVar* n) {
7873  //set parents
7874  n->set_parent(this);
7875 
7876  variables[position - variables.begin()].reset(n);
7877 }
7878 
7879 /**
7880  * \brief Reset member to variables
7881  */
7882 void LocalListStatement::reset_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator position, std::shared_ptr<LocalVar> n) {
7883  //set parents
7884  n->set_parent(this);
7885 
7886  variables[position - variables.begin()] = n;
7887 }

8224  /// copy constructor implementation
8225  Include::Include(const Include& obj) {
8226  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
8227  if (obj.filename) {
8228  this->filename.reset(obj.filename->clone());
8229  }
8230  /// copy each element of vector
8231  for (auto& item : obj.blocks) {
8232  this->blocks.emplace_back(item->clone());
8233  }
8234 
8235  /// if there is a token, make copy
8236  if (obj.token) {
8237  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
8238  }

8251  }

8254  item->set_parent(this);

8256  }

9517  /// copy constructor implementation
9518  IfStatement::IfStatement(const IfStatement& obj) {
9519  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
9520  if (obj.condition) {
9521  this->condition.reset(obj.condition->clone());
9522  }
9523  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
9524  if (obj.statement_block) {
9525  this->statement_block.reset(obj.statement_block->clone());
9526  }
9527  /// copy each element of vector
9528  for (auto& item : obj.elseifs) {
9529  this->elseifs.emplace_back(item->clone());
9530  }
9531  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
9532  if (obj.elses) {
9533  this->elses.reset(obj.elses->clone());
9534  }
9535 
9536  /// if there is a token, make copy
9537  if (obj.token) {
9538  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
9539  }
9540 
9541  /// set parents
9542  set_parent_in_children();
9543  }

9555  statement_block->set_parent(this);
9556  }

9559  item->set_parent(this);

9866 /**
9867  * \brief Erase member to statements
9868  */
9869 WatchVector::const_iterator WatchStatement::erase_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator first) {
9870  return statements.erase(first);
9871 }
9872 /**
9873  * \brief Erase members to statements
9874  */
9875 WatchVector::const_iterator WatchStatement::erase_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator first, WatchVector::const_iterator last) {
9876  return statements.erase(first, last);
9877 }
9878 /**
9879  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to statements
9880  *
9881  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
9882  */
9883 size_t WatchStatement::erase_watch(std::unordered_set<Watch*>& to_be_erased) {
9884  auto first = statements.begin();
9885  auto last = statements.end();
9886  auto result = first;
9887 
9888  while (first != last) {
9889  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
9890  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
9891  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
9892  reset_watch(result, *first);
9893  ++result;
9894  }
9895  ++first;
9896  }
9897 
9898  size_t out = last - result;
9899  erase_watch(result, last);
9900 
9901  return out;
9902 }

9908  n->set_parent(this);
9909  return statements.insert(position, n);
9910 }

9914  */
9915 void WatchStatement::reset_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator position, Watch* n) {
9916  //set parents
9917  n->set_parent(this);
9918 
9919  statements[position - statements.begin()].reset(n);
9920 }

10517  void ReactionStatement::visit_children(visitor::Visitor& v) {

10521  /// use . for object member
10522  op.accept(v);
10523  (void)v;
10524  /// optional member could be nullptr
10525  if (this->reaction2) {
10526  this->reaction2->accept(v);
10527  }
10528  (void)v;
10529  /// use -> for pointer member
10530  expression1->accept(v);
10531  (void)v;
10532  /// optional member could be nullptr
10533  if (this->expression2) {
10534  this->expression2->accept(v);
10535  }
10536  (void)v;
10537  }

10583  }

10585  this->op = obj.op;
10586  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
10587  if (obj.reaction2) {
10588  this->reaction2.reset(obj.reaction2->clone());
10589  }
10590  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
10591  if (obj.expression1) {
10592  this->expression1.reset(obj.expression1->clone());
10593  }

10595  if (obj.expression2) {
10596  this->expression2.reset(obj.expression2->clone());
10597  }

10600  if (obj.token) {
10601  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
10602  }
10603 
10604  /// set parents

10606  }

11318  item->accept(v);
11319  }

11323  item->accept(v);

11329  }

11334  }

11786 /**
11787  * \brief Erase member to variables
11788  */
11789 GlobalVarVector::const_iterator Global::erase_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator first) {
11790  return variables.erase(first);
11791 }
11792 /**
11793  * \brief Erase members to variables
11794  */
11795 GlobalVarVector::const_iterator Global::erase_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator first, GlobalVarVector::const_iterator last) {
11796  return variables.erase(first, last);
11797 }
11798 /**
11799  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to variables
11800  *
11801  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
11802  */
11803 size_t Global::erase_global_var(std::unordered_set<GlobalVar*>& to_be_erased) {
11804  auto first = variables.begin();
11805  auto last = variables.end();
11806  auto result = first;
11807 
11808  while (first != last) {
11809  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
11810  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
11811  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
11812  reset_global_var(result, *first);
11813  ++result;
11814  }
11815  ++first;
11816  }
11817 
11818  size_t out = last - result;
11819  erase_global_var(result, last);
11820 
11821  return out;
11822 }
11823

11825  * \brief Insert member to variables
11826  */
11827 GlobalVarVector::const_iterator Global::insert_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator position, const std::shared_ptr<GlobalVar>& n) {
11828  n->set_parent(this);
11829  return variables.insert(position, n);
11830 }

11834  */

11836  //set parents
11837  n->set_parent(this);
11838 
11839  variables[position - variables.begin()].reset(n);
11840 }

12573 /**
12574  * \brief Erase member to blocks
12575  */
12576 NodeVector::const_iterator Program::erase_node(NodeVector::const_iterator first) {
12577  return blocks.erase(first);
12578 }
12579 /**
12580  * \brief Erase members to blocks
12581  */
12582 NodeVector::const_iterator Program::erase_node(NodeVector::const_iterator first, NodeVector::const_iterator last) {
12583  return blocks.erase(first, last);
12584 }
12585 /**
12586  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to blocks
12587  *
12588  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
12589  */
12590 size_t Program::erase_node(std::unordered_set<Node*>& to_be_erased) {
12591  auto first = blocks.begin();
12592  auto last = blocks.end();
12593  auto result = first;
12594 
12595  while (first != last) {
12596  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
12597  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
12598  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
12599  reset_node(result, *first);
12600  ++result;
12601  }
12602  ++first;
12603  }
12604 
12605  size_t out = last - result;
12606  erase_node(result, last);
12607 
12608  return out;
12609 }
12610 
12611 /**
12612  * \brief Insert member to blocks
12613  */
12614 NodeVector::const_iterator Program::insert_node(NodeVector::const_iterator position, const std::shared_ptr<Node>& n) {
12615  n->set_parent(this);
12616  return blocks.insert(position, n);
12617 }
12618 
12619 /**
12620  * \brief Reset member to blocks
12621  */
12622 void Program::reset_node(NodeVector::const_iterator position, Node* n) {
12623  //set parents
12624  n->set_parent(this);
12625 
12626  blocks[position - blocks.begin()].reset(n);
12627 }
12628 
12629 /**

12631  */
12632 void Program::reset_node(NodeVector::const_iterator position, std::shared_ptr<Node> n) {
12633  //set parents

12635 
12636  blocks[position - blocks.begin()] = n;
12637 }
